This paper focuses on designing a semi-autonomous UAV system for emergency response scenarios, which involves a complex interplay between human control and drone autonomy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Robotics (cs.RO) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the need to balance mission functionality with safety, which is a key concern in the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. Finally, the paper uses a participatory design process and SA cards to equip domain experts with SA knowledge, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
